{{S-end}}

==Lachoneus II, son of Lachoneus==
'''Lachoneus II''', son of the above Lachoneus, succeeded his father as chief judge. He reigned for one year before the [[king-men]] assassinated him as part of an attempt to establish a monarchy. The monarchy was never established nor a new judge instated; the central government instead crumbled to be replaced by a tribal structure ({{Sourcetext|source=Book of Mormon|book=3 Nephi|chapter=6|verse=19|range=}}, {{Sourcetext|source=Book of Mormon|book=3 Nephi|chapter=7|verse=1|range=-4|nobook=}}).

Lachoneus II is the last Nephite ruler specifically identified in the Book of Mormon. 

