In [[demonology]], '''Vepar''' is a strong Great Duke of [[Hell]], and rules twenty-nine legions of [[demon]]s. <!-- HISTORICAL SOURCES SAY HE, *NOT* SHE -->He<!-- HISTORICAL SOURCES SAY HE, *NOT* SHE --> governs the waters and guides armoured ships laden with ammunition and weapons; <!-- HISTORICAL SOURCES SAY HE, *NOT* SHE -->he<!-- HISTORICAL SOURCES SAY HE, *NOT* SHE --> can also make, if requested, the sea rough and stormy, and to appear full of ships. Vepar can make men die in three days by putrefying sores and wounds, causing worms to breed in them, but if requested by the conjurer he can heal them immediately.

Vepar is depicted as a [[mermaid]].

''Other spellings'': Separ, Vephar.

