'''WLGI''', known as "Radio [[Bahá'í Faith|Bahá'í]]", is licensed to [[Hemingway, South Carolina]], and broadcasts at 90.9 FM. The station broadcasts a variety of programming, both religious and secular. The station is licensed by the FCC for noncommercial Class C operation and is operated by the Louis G. Gregory Bahá'í Institute,<ref>[http://www.radio-locator.com/cgi-bin/finder?sr=Y&call=WLGI Radio-Locator. Retrieved April 24, 2007.]</ref> named after [[Hand of the Cause]] [[Louis George Gregory]], a prominent African-American Bahá'í.
See [[The Bahá'í Faith in South Carolina]].
